WEBVTT

00:04.482 --> 00:05.875
Previously onSEAL Team...

00:05.918 --> 00:08.095
I'm Lieutenant Commander
Williams, the JAG assigned

00:08.138 --> 00:09.226
to your defense.FLORES:
Master Chief Hayes is accused

00:09.270 --> 00:10.793
of voluntary manslaughter
for shooting

00:10.836 --> 00:13.187
Yazeed Nafal,
an unarmed Jordanian civilian

00:13.230 --> 00:15.624
Exhibit 3: cell phone footage
of the shooting.

00:15.667 --> 00:17.974
[gunshots over video]

00:18.018 --> 00:19.802
Command has issued
a no-contact order.

00:19.845 --> 00:21.195
You are to stay away
from each other and from Jason.

00:21.238 --> 00:23.719
My detailer called,
said that I should hear back

00:23.762 --> 00:25.242
about that Echo job
by next month.

00:25.286 --> 00:27.636
I'm pregnant.DAVIS:
She deserves a response.

00:27.679 --> 00:29.681
NAIMIA:
What do you need a lawyer for?

00:29.725 --> 00:31.553
The i-investigation involves
classified information.

00:31.596 --> 00:32.815
Why are you holding out on me?

00:32.858 --> 00:34.643
What happened to Sonny
wasn't on you.

00:34.686 --> 00:36.340
Everything falls on Bravo 1.

00:36.384 --> 00:37.733
Trial counsel
found out that, uh,

00:37.776 --> 00:39.343
Raqqa Jacques
was Ray's torturer.

00:39.387 --> 00:42.303
They think I shot an
unarmed man out of revenge.

00:42.346 --> 00:44.392
They upped the charges
to murder.

00:46.394 --> 00:48.918
WILLIAMS:Chief Warrant Officer Ray Perry
has already testified

00:48.961 --> 00:50.659
that when you found out
about Raqqa Jacques,

00:50.702 --> 00:52.269
you were determined
to get revenge on his behalf.

00:52.313 --> 00:53.792
That's not accurate.

00:53.836 --> 00:55.403
So much so that you charged
into that building

00:55.446 --> 00:56.969
loaded for bear and shot
the first man you saw.

00:57.013 --> 00:58.667
Look, it was a routine op.

00:58.710 --> 01:00.190
So it's routine for you
to murder unarmed civilians

01:00.234 --> 01:01.844
on operations?I didn't murder anybody.

01:01.887 --> 01:03.846
This is what they do.

01:03.889 --> 01:05.935
Push your buttons
to make you look volatile.

01:05.978 --> 01:07.806
All right, look, can we just runit again until I get it right?

01:07.850 --> 01:09.286
Keep running it.

01:09.330 --> 01:11.027
There's a reason most defendants
don't take the stand.

01:11.071 --> 01:12.507
Well, I'm gonna look more
guilty if I don't say anything,

01:12.550 --> 01:14.030
so I got to say something.

01:14.074 --> 01:15.814
The judge will instruct
the panel that not testifying

01:15.858 --> 01:17.512
is not an admission of guilt.

01:17.555 --> 01:20.080
I'd recommend the same to any
client facing a murder charge.

01:20.123 --> 01:21.516
[grunts softly]

01:23.431 --> 01:25.433
♪

01:34.442 --> 01:37.053
After Lindell comes Bravo.

01:37.097 --> 01:39.447
Uh, Spenser, Quinn,Sawyer, Reynolds, Carter,

01:39.490 --> 01:40.926
will all take the stand.

01:40.970 --> 01:42.406
What about Ray?

01:42.450 --> 01:44.104
He'll testify, but he's takenan immunity deal.

01:44.147 --> 01:46.106
Immunity from what?

01:46.149 --> 01:48.717
Dad's other teammates
didn't take any deals.

01:48.760 --> 01:50.284
Since Chief Warrant Officer
Perry was the OIC

01:50.327 --> 01:52.373
during the op in question,
the UCMJ

01:52.416 --> 01:54.679
could technically charge him--
regardless of the outcome

01:54.723 --> 01:56.507
of the trial-- with Article 92,

01:56.551 --> 01:58.248
failure to obeya lawful regulation.

01:58.292 --> 02:00.032
I'm sure the prosecution

02:00.076 --> 02:01.991
presented him with immunity, uh,

02:02.034 --> 02:03.732
in exchange for him
being on their witness list.

02:03.775 --> 02:05.168
Well, if he's working
with the prosecution

02:05.212 --> 02:06.996
that means he's gonna have
to testify against me.

02:07.039 --> 02:09.346
That's it.I don't know.

02:09.390 --> 02:11.131
I read his deposition
after it was unsealed.

02:11.174 --> 02:12.871
His answers
are deliberately vague.

02:12.915 --> 02:14.960
He was walking
a semantic tightrope.

02:15.004 --> 02:16.136
But he'll be
forced to take

02:16.179 --> 02:17.441
a strong position
in court, won't he?

02:17.485 --> 02:18.921
They'll want to use
your father's friendship

02:18.964 --> 02:20.531
to push the revenge angle,

02:20.575 --> 02:22.838
dramatize Chief WarrantOfficer Perry's captivity

02:22.881 --> 02:25.884
and say that his torture
was your father's motive

02:25.928 --> 02:28.365
to kill an unarmed man.
I think you should go
get some sodas for us.

02:28.409 --> 02:29.975
Dad, I can handle this.No, I think that you should go.

02:30.019 --> 02:30.976
I can do this.

02:31.020 --> 02:31.977
Luckily,this won't be tried

02:32.021 --> 02:33.544
in the court of public opinion,

02:33.588 --> 02:35.677
so you and your family won't get
dragged through the mud.

02:35.720 --> 02:37.157
The U.S. may bescapegoating you,

02:37.200 --> 02:38.245
but no one wantsthis situation to get out.

02:38.288 --> 02:40.334
Total media blackout.

02:40.377 --> 02:41.726
Oh, that's too bad.
I was really hoping

02:41.770 --> 02:43.598
to launch my T-shirt line
on 60 Minutes.

02:43.641 --> 02:45.252
WILLIAMS:No gallery, no teammates.

02:45.295 --> 02:46.601
No family. Not until
the verdict is announced.

02:46.644 --> 02:48.385
Sorry, Emma.

02:48.429 --> 02:49.691
[quietly]:
It's okay.

02:49.734 --> 02:51.780
The good news is you
have a lot of support.

02:51.823 --> 02:53.869
Unparalleled success
with high-profile missions.

02:53.912 --> 02:55.436
An otherwise peerless record.

02:55.479 --> 02:56.698
That's now been trashed.

02:56.741 --> 02:58.221
I've gathered

02:58.265 --> 03:01.485
over a dozen references
from past teammates.

03:07.491 --> 03:08.666
Great work.

03:08.710 --> 03:10.929
Thanks.Havinga "good sailor" book

03:10.973 --> 03:12.496
full of rave character reviews
are just the thing we'll need

03:12.540 --> 03:14.933
for leniency with the panel
in case of sentencing.

03:14.977 --> 03:16.108
Sentencing?

03:16.152 --> 03:17.153
Bad enough

03:17.197 --> 03:18.502
that the Navythinks I'm guilty.

03:18.546 --> 03:20.548
Now I have the two of you
convicting me.

03:26.771 --> 03:29.513
[music playing softly]

03:29.557 --> 03:32.212
[Stella grunting]

03:32.255 --> 03:36.433
Hey, um, I don't know
how this is all going to fit.

03:36.477 --> 03:38.522
I can't believe I accumulatedso much stuff.

03:38.566 --> 03:41.656
[sighs] Well, I can't believe
that I asked a hoarder

03:41.699 --> 03:42.961
to move in with me.

03:43.005 --> 03:45.399
Forgive me
for being sentimental,

03:45.442 --> 03:46.617
but you know, you never know

03:46.661 --> 03:48.010
what you're gonna
fall in love with again.

03:48.053 --> 03:49.403
Right?

03:49.446 --> 03:51.013
Did you just compare me
to this...

03:51.056 --> 03:52.493
this crusty
Walden Pond souvenir?

03:52.536 --> 03:54.712
Okay, perhaps
I need to declutter.

03:54.756 --> 03:56.061
I think that's
a good idea.

03:56.105 --> 03:59.021
You should, uh,
you should probably cast away

03:59.064 --> 04:00.849
all remnants of life
before you met me.

04:00.892 --> 04:02.807
Same to you.

04:02.851 --> 04:04.896
Actually, you know what?
Maybe we should, um,

04:04.940 --> 04:07.508
give all of our stuffthe Marie Kondo treatment.

04:07.551 --> 04:09.249
That sounds like a martial art.

04:09.292 --> 04:11.947
No, it's when you're, uh,
supposed to hold something

04:11.990 --> 04:13.862
and see if it "sparks joy,"

04:13.905 --> 04:18.345
and if it doesn't spark joy,
then you throw it out.

04:18.388 --> 04:19.955
I think this sparks joy.

04:19.998 --> 04:22.131
Mm? Mm-hmm.Mm-hmm. Little bit.

04:22.174 --> 04:24.046
Mm-mm-mm.

04:25.047 --> 04:26.222
[phone ringing]

04:26.266 --> 04:29.051
[both grunting]

04:29.094 --> 04:30.618
It's Jace.

04:32.620 --> 04:35.100
Hey, brother, what's up?

04:35.144 --> 04:37.494
No.

04:37.538 --> 04:39.540
No, I haven't heard from him.

04:40.541 --> 04:42.238
Yeah, let me...

04:42.282 --> 04:44.109
I'll see where
his head's at.

04:45.328 --> 04:46.503
Okay.

04:48.288 --> 04:51.291
That sounded ominous.

04:51.334 --> 04:53.336
Jason's worried about
what Ray's gonna say in court.

04:53.380 --> 04:56.165
And Jason can't contact
Ray directly, so...

04:56.208 --> 04:58.341
Look, I... [chuckles]

04:58.385 --> 04:59.560
I know that, I know that we said

04:59.603 --> 05:00.778
we would spend today together.

05:00.822 --> 05:02.476
It's okay.
Do what you need to do.

05:02.519 --> 05:05.870
I have... a little bit
to keep me busy.

05:05.914 --> 05:07.307
You sure?

05:07.350 --> 05:08.699
Just a little bit.

05:08.743 --> 05:10.048
All right.Okay.

05:10.092 --> 05:11.876
I'll be back soon, okay?Okay.

05:11.920 --> 05:13.922
[aircraft whooshing]

05:17.708 --> 05:19.710
We need to go back
to your JAG's office.

05:19.754 --> 05:21.103
You can't run from this.

05:21.146 --> 05:23.714
You think I'm guilty?
What?

05:23.758 --> 05:25.325
I mean, do you think I'm guilty?

05:25.368 --> 05:28.763
The way the prosecution is
spinning this right now, I-I...

05:28.806 --> 05:30.199
completely get
why my own daughter

05:30.242 --> 05:31.809
would think that I'm guilty.

05:31.853 --> 05:33.550
I know you like
to do things the right way.

05:33.594 --> 05:35.291
That's why I came down here
to help you.

05:35.335 --> 05:37.424
And that's why
you need to prepare.Prepare.

05:37.467 --> 05:38.512
Prepare for what,
my whole career

05:38.555 --> 05:39.861
to be flushed
down the toilet?

05:39.904 --> 05:41.210
I can't even speak
in my own defense here.

05:41.253 --> 05:42.254
Well, Lieutenant Commander
Williams

05:42.298 --> 05:43.865
said that's normal.
Normal?

05:43.908 --> 05:45.649
Like your best friend stabbing
you in the back? That's normal?

05:45.693 --> 05:46.868
You don't know
what's going on with him,

05:46.911 --> 05:48.217
but he wouldn't do that.He wouldn't do that.

05:48.260 --> 05:49.392
Uncle Ray's family.

05:49.436 --> 05:51.394
You know, I hope you're right.

05:51.438 --> 05:53.091
'Cause never did
I think the Navy

05:53.135 --> 05:55.398
would be railroading me, either,
but here I am.

06:03.972 --> 06:05.190
[sniffles]

06:09.281 --> 06:11.240
Hey.

06:11.283 --> 06:12.937
Hey.What are you doing here?

06:12.981 --> 06:14.852
Just want to see how
you're holding up.

06:14.896 --> 06:18.160
[scoffs] I'm fine. What makes
you think I need checking up on?

06:18.203 --> 06:21.032
Well, maybe 'cause your best
friend's on trial for his life?

06:21.076 --> 06:22.512
Or maybe because,
as OIC on the op,

06:22.556 --> 06:24.253
if Jason goes down,
you could be at risk.

06:24.296 --> 06:26.473
In this job, we're always in the
crosshairs. I got it handled.

06:26.516 --> 06:28.039
You got it handled as in...
as in lawyering up

06:28.083 --> 06:29.258
and getting immunity?

06:30.912 --> 06:32.957
Look, team knows you didn't
do anything out of bounds.

06:33.001 --> 06:34.742
Okay? Neither did Jason.

06:36.047 --> 06:37.919
Just want to know
what's going on with you, man.

06:40.225 --> 06:42.750
What part of "no-contact order"
don't you understand, Clay?

06:44.708 --> 06:46.318
All right.

06:51.193 --> 06:54.849
♪ Sit here in the dark...

06:54.892 --> 06:57.721
HANNAH:
Sonny Quinn, what are you doing?

06:57.765 --> 07:00.463
Oh, uh, just taking a break.

07:00.507 --> 07:03.466
You know, I've defused bombs

07:03.510 --> 07:05.555
that are a lot less complicated
than this crib.

07:05.599 --> 07:07.209
[laughs]
Well, it's a good thing

07:07.252 --> 07:09.037
you have ten more weeks
to put it together.

07:09.080 --> 07:10.995
Yeah, well, it, uh,

07:11.039 --> 07:13.215
it might actually
take me that long.

07:13.258 --> 07:15.173
You know,
you're welcome here anytime.

07:15.217 --> 07:16.566
Lisa, too.

07:16.610 --> 07:19.917
Yeah. We'll definitely
take you up on that.

07:19.961 --> 07:21.702
[phone ringing]

07:22.833 --> 07:25.140
Oh, look at that.
Speak of the devil.

07:27.142 --> 07:28.317
Hey.

07:28.360 --> 07:29.405
DAVIS:
Hey.

07:29.449 --> 07:30.537
Your ears must've been burning.

07:30.580 --> 07:33.583
[laughs]Look at this right here.

07:33.627 --> 07:36.456
Is that crib still in pieces?

07:36.499 --> 07:38.240
[Hannah laughs]Yes, it is, okay?

07:38.283 --> 07:41.199
The damn Swedish Chef
wrote the directions.

07:41.243 --> 07:43.419
I told him he was
in over his head.

07:43.463 --> 07:45.334
[laughs]:
Hey, Hannah. How are you?

07:45.377 --> 07:46.988
I'm good.

07:47.031 --> 07:50.165
I'm, uh, trying to hire
a new manager at the bar.

07:50.208 --> 07:53.777
Hey, if you need anything,
um, we're here.

07:53.821 --> 07:56.040
Thanks, Lisa.

07:56.084 --> 07:58.042
I'll let you two catch up.Great. Thank you.

07:58.086 --> 07:59.261
Uh-- You okay?
I'm good.

07:59.304 --> 08:01.176
All right.

08:01.219 --> 08:03.265
Hey.

08:03.308 --> 08:04.745
Hi.

08:04.788 --> 08:06.529
I'm so sorry I had
to extend the trip,

08:06.573 --> 08:08.531
but, um, you know,
I didn't realize

08:08.575 --> 08:11.969
there was so much stuff to do
for one tiny human.

08:12.013 --> 08:12.970
How's everything going?

08:13.014 --> 08:15.190
Uh, well, I've almost finished

08:15.233 --> 08:18.062
collating the last of
the reports for the JAGs, and...

08:18.106 --> 08:20.238
I kind of wish
they'd just call me as a witness

08:20.282 --> 08:23.328
so I could defend
Jason publicly.

08:23.372 --> 08:24.939
[stammers]
The optics of working on behalf

08:24.982 --> 08:27.071
of the prosecution
does not look great.

08:27.115 --> 08:29.987
Well, that ain't your choice.
Echo knows that.

08:31.293 --> 08:33.513
You heard anything
on the new job?

08:33.556 --> 08:36.167
Not yet, but probably just
tangled up

08:36.211 --> 08:38.430
in the usual red tape.

08:38.474 --> 08:40.258
Them, uh, damn pencil pushers
better hurry their butts up

08:40.302 --> 08:42.434
because this right here, okay,

08:42.478 --> 08:44.436
has been a little classified
for too long.

08:44.480 --> 08:46.047
[laughs]

08:46.090 --> 08:47.614
DAVIS:
Mm... [chuckles]

08:47.657 --> 08:49.877
Right. I-I got to take Hannah

08:49.920 --> 08:53.837
to go see
the OB-GYN Kenobi doctor.

08:53.881 --> 08:55.360
Ah. No, I-I actually
have to go, too.

08:55.404 --> 08:57.014
We just got clearance
to complete

08:57.058 --> 09:00.365
the S.A. intel dossier
on Raqqa Jacques, so...

09:00.409 --> 09:02.193
Have fun with Hannah.

09:02.237 --> 09:04.587
I will. All right.
I'll call you later.

09:04.631 --> 09:06.589
Bye.Bye.

09:06.633 --> 09:08.373
WILLIAMS:The panel consists
of eight members.

09:08.417 --> 09:10.114
Three are enlisted
and two are battle-tested.

09:10.158 --> 09:11.812
They need three-fourths
to convict.

09:11.855 --> 09:13.857
The prosecution will want
to prove you're a loose cannon

09:13.901 --> 09:15.598
capable of war crimes.

09:15.642 --> 09:18.993
They'll have scoured through
every Bravo AAR and evaluation

09:19.036 --> 09:20.429
from the past two decades.

09:20.472 --> 09:21.691
What exactly
are they looking for?

09:21.735 --> 09:23.519
Violations of protocol,

09:23.563 --> 09:25.652
clashes between you
and other operators.

09:25.695 --> 09:29.307
Anything to show your emotions
overruled tactical judgement.

09:29.351 --> 09:31.571
If their plan is to make my dad
out to be a monster,

09:31.614 --> 09:32.746
what's our plan?

09:32.789 --> 09:34.617
Cite your father's track record.

09:34.661 --> 09:36.401
Highlight their shoddy
investigation.

09:36.445 --> 09:37.620
Discredit the bystander's

09:37.664 --> 09:39.056
incomplete video
of the shooting.

09:39.100 --> 09:40.623
You make it sound so easy.

09:40.667 --> 09:41.668
[knocking on door]

09:43.495 --> 09:45.759
Um, I'm sorry to interrupt,
Lieutenant Commander.

09:45.802 --> 09:47.804
I've got the Raqqa Jacques
dossier.

09:47.848 --> 09:50.067
I also wanted to share
something else with you.

09:50.111 --> 09:52.504
I was reviewing intel
from the Jordan op.

09:52.548 --> 09:56.160
That man with the tattoo holding
the AK, that's Yazeed Nafal.

09:56.204 --> 09:57.945
Whoa.

09:57.988 --> 09:59.033
Let me see that.

09:59.076 --> 10:00.861
EMMA:
That's the guy Dad shot.

10:02.210 --> 10:03.690
They said he was just a driver.

10:03.733 --> 10:05.430
In his recruitment
video, he calls for

10:05.474 --> 10:06.736
"death to the Western world."

10:06.780 --> 10:08.390
"Just a driver" my ass.

10:08.433 --> 10:10.174
I hope that helps.
WILLIAMS:
Excellent work.

10:11.523 --> 10:13.743
Davis, thanks.

10:13.787 --> 10:16.398
Good luck tomorrow.
We're all behind you.

10:19.183 --> 10:20.881
This is a game changer, right?

10:20.924 --> 10:23.274
Proving Nafal was an active
member of the AKM

10:23.318 --> 10:25.102
could demolish
the prosecution's case.

10:25.146 --> 10:26.364
Things are starting
to look up here.

10:26.408 --> 10:27.714
In the courtroom
tomorrow, remember,

10:27.757 --> 10:29.977
it's not just the facts
or your record on trial.

10:30.020 --> 10:32.240
The jury will be
watching you, too.

10:35.069 --> 10:37.158
So when JAG Flores
attacks your character,

10:37.201 --> 10:40.683
or a ruling goes against us,
you don't react.

10:40.727 --> 10:42.946
Stay calm in the chaos
and show the jury

10:42.990 --> 10:45.383
why they can trust you.

10:53.130 --> 10:55.263
All rise.

11:01.225 --> 11:03.575
Be seated, please.

11:05.665 --> 11:07.101
[gavel bangs twice]

11:07.144 --> 11:08.668
The court will now
come to order.

11:08.711 --> 11:10.495
Is the government prepared
to make an opening statement?

11:10.539 --> 11:12.759
Yes, Your Honor.
Permission to enter the well.

11:12.802 --> 11:14.717
Proceed.

11:14.761 --> 11:18.286
On 11 March, 2021,
while on a mission

11:18.329 --> 11:20.505
with SEAL Team Bravo
in Irbid, Jordan,

11:20.549 --> 11:23.552
Master Chief Jason Hayes
entered a residential building

11:23.595 --> 11:25.728
and shot and killed
Yazeed Nafal,

11:25.772 --> 11:27.861
an unarmed Jordanian civilian.

11:27.904 --> 11:30.385
The government will demonstrate
by means of video evidence,

11:30.428 --> 11:34.171
timeline and testimony that
Chief Hayes committed murder,

11:34.215 --> 11:36.826
motivated by revenge
on behalf of his best friend

11:36.870 --> 11:40.438
and fellow SEAL, Warrant Officer
Raymond Perry.

11:40.482 --> 11:42.136
This is a tragic event.

11:42.179 --> 11:43.790
While the government has
the utmost respect

11:43.833 --> 11:46.183
for Master Chief Hayes'
service to this country,

11:46.227 --> 11:48.751
he must be held accountable
for this heinous crime.

11:51.972 --> 11:54.583
The prosecution will tell you
that Master Chief Hayes

11:54.626 --> 11:56.280
went rogue.

11:56.324 --> 11:57.847
That he was overcome
with vengeance

11:57.891 --> 12:00.676
and shot an innocent man
in cold blood.

12:00.720 --> 12:02.460
Nonsense.

12:02.504 --> 12:05.681
It is Master Chief Hayes'
unwavering sworn statement

12:05.725 --> 12:09.163
that the deceased, Yazeed
Nafal, an AKM henchman,

12:09.206 --> 12:12.557
was holding an M1951 Beretta
in his left hand.

12:12.601 --> 12:14.821
The taking of a life
might be heinous

12:14.864 --> 12:17.301
to those of us fortunate enough

12:17.345 --> 12:19.260
to never have engaged
in combat,

12:19.303 --> 12:21.828
but the reality is that
Master Chief Hayes

12:21.871 --> 12:25.483
is wrongly on trial
for doing his job.

12:28.225 --> 12:29.923
Mr. Khalaf,
as the representative

12:29.966 --> 12:31.707
of Jordan's General
