will make us look desperate.

21:13.707 --> 21:15.883
I am desperate.It only took me

21:15.926 --> 21:18.451
three questions to get you
to self-destruct in prep.

21:18.494 --> 21:21.018
Flores is dying to get you on
his turf and push your buttons.

21:21.062 --> 21:23.107
My word should matter.

21:23.151 --> 21:24.761
If you blow up on the stand,

21:24.805 --> 21:26.981
your word will get you sent
away for the rest of your life.

21:28.199 --> 21:30.724
It's my ass on the line, ma'am.

21:38.384 --> 21:40.081
Do you solemnly swear or affirm
that the testimony

21:40.124 --> 21:41.561
you will give in this general
court-martial will be the truth,

21:41.604 --> 21:43.345
the whole truth
and nothing but the truth,

21:43.389 --> 21:46.000
under penalty of perjury?

21:46.043 --> 21:47.306
I do.

21:47.349 --> 21:48.437
Please be seated.

21:48.481 --> 21:49.525
State your name,

21:49.569 --> 21:50.961
rank and billet.Jason M. Hayes,

21:51.005 --> 21:52.789
Master Chief,
United States Navy.

21:52.833 --> 21:54.748
Navy Special Warfare
Development Group.

21:54.791 --> 21:56.967
Bravo Team Leader.It's your witness.

21:59.187 --> 22:00.928
Master Chief,
walk me through what happened

22:00.971 --> 22:02.538
in Irbid on 11 March.

22:02.582 --> 22:04.235
Bravo Team arrived
on target.

22:04.279 --> 22:07.761
My teammates
observed two men

22:07.804 --> 22:11.199
enter an apartment complex,
one shouldering an AK.

22:11.242 --> 22:13.244
Because they were armed,

22:13.288 --> 22:16.204
we entered the apartment complex
with our pistols drawn.

22:16.247 --> 22:18.467
Surely it was chaos the moment
you entered the building.

22:18.511 --> 22:20.513
How are you able
to recall what happened

22:20.556 --> 22:22.863
during such a kinetic operation?

22:22.906 --> 22:25.039
We're trained to do this.

22:25.082 --> 22:26.780
It's our job.

22:26.823 --> 22:29.478
We remain calm in the chaos.

22:29.522 --> 22:31.654
It's like time slows down.

22:31.698 --> 22:33.308
I led my team
up the stairs.

22:33.352 --> 22:34.918
I was the tip of the spear.
I rounded a corner.

22:34.962 --> 22:37.181
I looked up, I saw a male--

22:37.225 --> 22:39.270
black hair, track jacket.

22:39.314 --> 22:41.098
Had a gun on his side
in his left hand.

22:41.142 --> 22:44.058
It was a Beretta M1951.

22:44.101 --> 22:47.453
Before he could alert
the others, I shot him.

22:48.541 --> 22:52.022
I continued into the target,
and I completed my duty.

22:52.066 --> 22:53.894
No further questions.

22:53.937 --> 22:55.069
Is there cross-examination?

22:55.112 --> 22:56.766
Yes, Your Honor.

22:58.551 --> 22:59.987
So, Master Chief Hayes,
your duty,

23:00.030 --> 23:01.641
as you put it,
is to kill people?

23:01.684 --> 23:03.251
You got that backwards.

23:03.294 --> 23:06.210
My job is to save lives,
not take them.

23:06.254 --> 23:09.736
Like the hundreds of innocent
people that Bravo Team saved

23:09.779 --> 23:11.694
by stopping AKM terrorists

23:11.738 --> 23:12.956
from taking out
two commercial airliners.

23:13.000 --> 23:14.218
Speaking of
innocent people,

23:14.262 --> 23:15.916
I'd like to concentrate
on the very real,

23:15.959 --> 23:18.658
and very dead, unarmed
Jordanian citizen, Mr. Nafal.

23:18.701 --> 23:20.486
Is he the first unarmed man
you've killed?

23:20.529 --> 23:21.617
Objection.

23:21.661 --> 23:22.662
Sustained.

23:22.705 --> 23:23.706
How many people have you killed?

23:23.750 --> 23:24.707
That's not something
I think about.

23:24.751 --> 23:26.666
Is that because
after 20 years

23:26.709 --> 23:27.710
you've become
indifferent to killing?

23:27.754 --> 23:28.711
It's because
I know what it means

23:28.755 --> 23:29.843
to take a human life.

23:29.886 --> 23:32.411
Chief Warrant Officer Perry
testified

23:32.454 --> 23:34.413
that you learned
of the HVT's identity

23:34.456 --> 23:36.197
a few hours
before the Irbid op.

23:36.240 --> 23:38.329
That's correct.

23:38.373 --> 23:40.897
You rescued Warrant Officer
Perry from his torture chamber.

23:40.941 --> 23:43.117
You witnessed his ordeal,

23:43.160 --> 23:44.466
and his condition,
first hand?

23:44.510 --> 23:45.641
I did.

23:45.685 --> 23:47.774
That must have been difficult.

23:47.817 --> 23:50.298
If I had been in your position,
I would absolutely want justice

23:50.341 --> 23:51.560
for what was done
to my best friend.

23:51.604 --> 23:52.779
With all due respect, sir,

23:52.822 --> 23:54.128
you've never been
in my position.

23:54.171 --> 23:56.217
Are you telling me
this bombshell about the HVT

23:56.260 --> 23:57.784
didn't cause you to conflate
your personal feelings

23:57.827 --> 23:58.915
and your professional duty?

23:58.959 --> 24:01.048
It's always personal.

24:01.091 --> 24:02.441
The war on
terror started

24:02.484 --> 24:04.399
when 3,000
of our fellow Americans

24:04.443 --> 24:06.749
were killed on our own soil.

24:06.793 --> 24:08.490
They hit us,

24:08.534 --> 24:10.100
so we hit them back.

24:10.144 --> 24:12.146
There's nothing impersonal
about it.So you're admitting

24:12.189 --> 24:13.277
emotion clouded your judgment

24:13.321 --> 24:14.409
and led you to kill
an unarmed man?

24:14.453 --> 24:16.324
Mr. Nafal had a gun.

24:16.367 --> 24:18.631
Clearly a man willing to
compromise his morals to kill

24:18.674 --> 24:20.067
must be willing to lie, too.

24:20.110 --> 24:21.068
Objection.

24:21.111 --> 24:22.504
Overruled.

24:22.548 --> 24:24.463
Answer the question,
Master Chief.

24:26.900 --> 24:28.989
The war on terror has come
at a heavy price.

24:29.032 --> 24:31.600
It's cost me my family,

24:31.644 --> 24:34.124
my teammates, my marriage,

24:34.168 --> 24:37.432
seeing my kids grow up.

24:37.476 --> 24:39.739
But the one thing
that it hasn't taken from me

24:39.782 --> 24:42.829
is my honor and my word.

24:42.872 --> 24:47.355
I wouldn't disrespect
the Trident to protect myself.

24:47.398 --> 24:50.445
Lying would be
a betrayal to my men

24:50.489 --> 24:53.361
and the country I love to serve.

24:55.058 --> 24:57.321
I only have one more question.

24:57.365 --> 24:59.149
Master Chief Hayes...

25:01.108 --> 25:02.892
...where's the gun?

25:03.893 --> 25:06.113
♪

25:09.551 --> 25:11.118
Hey.

25:11.161 --> 25:13.033
Ain't you a sight
for sore eyes?

25:13.076 --> 25:15.339
Well, right back at you,
sailor.
Yeah.

25:18.691 --> 25:20.388
This damn trial.

25:20.431 --> 25:23.260
Uh, it's bad enough that
they're stringing up Jace

25:23.304 --> 25:25.698
for some BS and...

25:25.741 --> 25:28.744
you and I got to
tiptoe around all...

25:28.788 --> 25:31.399
these extra eyeballs on Bravo.Yeah.

25:31.442 --> 25:33.880
None of this is easy.WOMAN:
Hey.

25:33.923 --> 25:35.534
I, uh...

25:35.577 --> 25:38.449
