back to normal.

25:38.493 --> 25:40.277
Normal?

25:41.278 --> 25:43.280
So, how did it go in court?

25:43.324 --> 25:44.630
Oh, it was all a joke.

25:44.673 --> 25:46.109
They kept picking apart
every minute of the day

25:46.153 --> 25:47.546
leading up to the op.

25:47.589 --> 25:48.982
Hardly anything
that really matters.

25:50.070 --> 25:52.289
Ah, maybe we should be
doing that.

25:52.333 --> 25:54.465
What?I mean,
maybe we've been

25:54.509 --> 25:56.424
so focused on the day
of the shooting

25:56.467 --> 25:58.861
that we've been missing
the whole picture.

26:01.385 --> 26:02.909
I got to head back
to the office.

26:02.952 --> 26:04.301
Uh, I'm s...
Don't wait up.

26:04.345 --> 26:05.999
No. Oh.
Sorry.

26:07.043 --> 26:08.131
You're killing me.

26:08.175 --> 26:09.393
Literally.

26:10.438 --> 26:11.961
What's this?

26:12.005 --> 26:13.659
I'm making linguini.
Ha!

26:13.702 --> 26:15.356
'Guini, my favorite.

26:15.399 --> 26:17.010
Don't get your hopes up.

26:17.053 --> 26:19.316
I haven't perfected
the parmesan-to-butter ratio

26:19.360 --> 26:20.666
like Mom did.

26:20.709 --> 26:22.929
Mom's recipe, too, huh?Yeah.

26:22.972 --> 26:24.452
Ah, that's
a good last supper to have.

26:24.495 --> 26:26.715
It's not funny.It's a little funny,

26:26.759 --> 26:28.630
don't you think?
I think it's funny.

26:28.674 --> 26:30.893
JAG Williams called and said
Uncle Ray and your testimony

26:30.937 --> 26:33.156
made a big dent
in the prosecution's case.

26:33.200 --> 26:34.810
Still have that,
uh, video evidence.

26:34.854 --> 26:36.812
And it's my word
against theirs, so...

26:36.856 --> 26:39.119
Mm-hmm.
[sighs]

26:40.163 --> 26:42.296
I just want you to know that,
you know, I did the right thing.

26:43.732 --> 26:45.386
Never doubted that for a second.

26:50.173 --> 26:53.046
Em?
Hmm?

26:53.089 --> 26:54.656
You know, if I do go away,
you-you're gonna have to be

26:54.700 --> 26:57.485
Mikey's guardian.No, we're not thinking
about that.

26:57.528 --> 26:59.661
I know that
it's difficult

26:59.705 --> 27:01.794
to talk about these
times of things, Em.
Mm.

27:01.837 --> 27:03.752
I-I... That I get,

27:03.796 --> 27:05.667
but you know what,
you're...

27:05.711 --> 27:07.800
Okay.Come on, you're gonna be
able to handle this, okay?

27:07.843 --> 27:09.889
Handle you going to jail? How?

27:09.932 --> 27:11.673
Look, you're a strong,
young woman.

27:11.717 --> 27:13.240
You know what, you kept
this family together.

27:13.283 --> 27:14.241
after Mom.

27:14.284 --> 27:15.851
Okay.

27:15.895 --> 27:17.636
You've always been able to
manage without having me around

27:17.679 --> 27:18.985
most of your life.

27:19.028 --> 27:20.421
You-you kept the family
together.

27:20.464 --> 27:21.596
Why do you always
do that?

27:21.640 --> 27:22.728
What?

27:22.771 --> 27:24.381
Acting like
the only value you have is

27:24.425 --> 27:26.296
to your team
on the battlefield.

27:26.340 --> 27:28.385
I don't care what you think.

27:28.429 --> 27:29.865
You're the only parent
I have left.

27:29.909 --> 27:31.040
I'm always gonna need you.

27:31.084 --> 27:32.302
Look, I'm sorry.

27:32.346 --> 27:33.652
Hey.

27:33.695 --> 27:34.870
[softly]:They can't take you away
from me.

27:34.914 --> 27:36.698
[chuckles]:
They're not. Don't. Hey.

27:36.742 --> 27:38.482
Hey. Shh.

27:38.526 --> 27:40.223
[sobbing softly]

27:40.267 --> 27:41.834
They won't.

27:49.145 --> 27:50.669
[sighs]

27:54.150 --> 27:56.152
♪

28:00.113 --> 28:02.115
[exhales]

28:07.642 --> 28:09.644
[clicking slowly]

28:19.001 --> 28:20.307
[sets mug down]

28:25.660 --> 28:27.662
[line rings]

28:27.706 --> 28:29.359
Lt. Commander Williams,

28:29.403 --> 28:30.752
I'm sorry to be calling you
so early.

28:30.796 --> 28:32.754
♪

28:33.973 --> 28:36.149
This photo of Yazeed
Nafal was taken

28:36.192 --> 28:39.065
by Chief Petty Officer
Mina Hassan in Irbid, Jordan,

28:39.108 --> 28:41.894
48 hours before he was shot
by Master Chief Hayes.

28:41.937 --> 28:43.765
There is a gun tucked
into Nafal's waistband

28:43.809 --> 28:45.027
on the left side.

28:45.071 --> 28:47.856
The grip is consistent
with an M1951 Beretta.

28:47.900 --> 28:49.553
The gun described
by Master Chief Hayes.

28:49.597 --> 28:51.599
Yes, ma'am, the very same.

28:53.906 --> 28:56.038
FLORES:
What matters is the evidence.

28:56.082 --> 28:58.432
A video of Master Chief Hayes
shooting an unarmed man

28:58.475 --> 28:59.868
without provocation.

28:59.912 --> 29:02.871
The defense provided
a partial image of the grip

29:02.915 --> 29:05.352
of a pistol from two days
before the killing.

29:05.395 --> 29:07.702
This is purely circumstantial
and cannot put a gun

29:07.746 --> 29:09.660
in the victim's hand
at the time of his death.

29:09.704 --> 29:12.011
The government asks
that you find the accused

29:12.054 --> 29:13.752
guilty as charged.

29:18.582 --> 29:21.150
Lieutenant Commander Williams.

29:27.809 --> 29:30.029
You've seen the photo
of the gun.

29:30.072 --> 29:32.422
You've heard the testimony
of the sailors

29:32.466 --> 29:35.208
who stood alongside
Master Chief Hayes,

29:35.251 --> 29:38.951
who applaud his good standing
and honorable reputation.

29:38.994 --> 29:41.127
And you've heard
the sworn statement

29:41.170 --> 29:42.955
of Master Chief Hayes himself.

29:42.998 --> 29:44.173
Master Chief Hayes,

29:44.217 --> 29:45.958
in many ways,

29:46.001 --> 29:49.439
is the embodiment
of the war on terror.

29:49.483 --> 29:52.007
For over 20 years he's run
into the fire for his country.

29:52.051 --> 29:54.575
While the prosecution
has gone to great lengths

29:54.618 --> 29:56.707
to portray Master Chief Hayes
as a killer,

29:56.751 --> 29:58.361
I've learned--

29:58.405 --> 30:00.799
and I hope you have, too--

30:00.842 --> 30:03.279
that Master Chief Hayes
doesn't do his job

30:03.323 --> 30:05.238
to shoot the enemy
in front of him.

30:05.281 --> 30:08.023
He does it to protect
the people behind him.

30:08.067 --> 30:11.244
Not just his teammates
but his countrymen.

30:11.287 --> 30:13.724
And despite all he's sacrificed

30:13.768 --> 30:16.858
and the deep, personal price
he's paid,

30:16.902 --> 30:20.601
Master Chief Hayes has never
asked for anything in return.

30:20.644 --> 30:22.777
So I'll ask for him.

30:22.821 --> 30:27.303
If you're willing to trust
him with your freedom,

30:27.347 --> 30:30.524
please also trust his word.

30:35.703 --> 30:37.705
♪

30:44.712 --> 30:46.714
♪

30:53.939 --> 30:55.723
Has the panel reached a verdict?

30:56.942 --> 30:58.073
Yes, we have, Your Honor.

31:07.909 --> 31:10.651
We find the defendant,
Master Chief Jason M. Hayes...

31:11.695 --> 31:13.610
...not guilty.

31:15.656 --> 31:16.962
Thank you.

31:17.005 --> 31:20.095
It was my honor, Master Chief.

31:30.714 --> 31:33.065
There you go.
Thank you.

31:33.108 --> 31:34.893
SONNY:
Oh, what we got here?

31:34.936 --> 31:36.024
[chuckles]Hey now.

31:36.068 --> 31:37.808
NAIMA:All hail
the conquering hero.

31:37.852 --> 31:39.549
Hey, how are you?Mm.

31:39.593 --> 31:41.551
Thank you. You didn't have
to do all this, you know.

31:41.595 --> 31:42.988
All you been through?

31:43.031 --> 31:44.598
Couldn't get the champagne
on ice fast enough.

31:44.641 --> 31:46.469
JAG Flores found
out what happens

31:46.513 --> 31:48.210
when you mess
with the great Jason Hayes, huh?

31:48.254 --> 31:49.864
Thanks, man,
appreciate you all.

31:49.908 --> 31:51.474
I really do.
Thanks for, uh, being there

31:51.518 --> 31:53.694
and standing by me
with the support.

31:53.737 --> 31:55.348
All of you, thanks.

31:55.391 --> 31:56.523
Thank you.

31:56.566 --> 31:58.046
RAY:
Bravo 1.

31:59.526 --> 32:01.267
Welcome back.

32:03.051 --> 32:05.271
[laughter]

32:05.314 --> 32:07.099
Love you, brother, hey.Love you back.

32:07.142 --> 32:09.492
Appreciate you, I really do.

32:09.536 --> 32:11.320
Thanks for what you did
up there on the stand.

32:11.364 --> 32:12.974
All I did was tell the truth.

32:13.018 --> 32:14.541
Yeah, but...

32:14.584 --> 32:15.934
going kinetic.

32:15.977 --> 32:18.284
Maybe I did pusha little too hard.
Mm.

32:18.327 --> 32:19.938
I was the OIC.

32:19.981 --> 32:21.591
You didn't make me do anything
I didn't want to.

32:21.635 --> 32:23.680
Okay.

32:23.724 --> 32:25.552
Chief Warrant Officer Perry.

32:25.595 --> 32:28.424
[chuckles] I'm just glad
the truth finally prevailed.

32:29.730 --> 32:32.254
Not sure I could've kept on
without you.

32:33.734 --> 32:35.214
Good thing
I'm not going anywhere.

32:35.257 --> 32:37.042
[bottles clank]

32:37.085 --> 32:39.914
Mm.
Hey, where's Stella?

32:39.958 --> 32:42.047
She, uh, she had a lot
of papers to grade.
Mm.

32:42.090 --> 32:44.353
Look, man.

32:44.397 --> 32:46.486
The way I handled everything...

32:46.529 --> 32:47.966
No worries, man.

32:48.009 --> 32:49.619
You were just looking
after your team leader here.

32:49.663 --> 32:51.447
Shouldn't have doubted you.

32:51.491 --> 32:53.754
Just, uh, Jason in
DoD's crosshairs,

32:53.797 --> 32:55.799
I lost track of... everything

32:55.843 --> 32:57.845
that you've been through
these last few months, too.

32:57.888 --> 32:59.890
JASON:
It's been a tough go

32:59.934 --> 33:02.023
for Bravo Team
since we got back from Tunisia.

33:02.067 --> 33:04.721
Yeah, I'm just glad
it's behind us.

33:04.765 --> 33:06.375
All of it.That's right.

33:06.419 --> 33:09.465
Hey, uh, not to upstage...

33:09.509 --> 33:12.207
Bravo 1 here, but, uh, I, uh,

33:12.251 --> 33:14.775
I got some big news myself.

33:14.818 --> 33:16.385
The McRib's back already?

33:16.429 --> 33:18.039
[laughter]

33:19.649 --> 33:22.391
Uh... I'm gonna be a dad.

33:22.435 --> 33:23.784
What?

33:23.827 --> 33:25.481
Yeah.

33:26.961 --> 33:28.571
JASON:
Sonny Quinn's gonna be

33:28.615 --> 33:30.747
a dad...Wait, uh, who's the lucky lady?

33:30.791 --> 33:32.706
And what time does
she get off stage?

33:32.749 --> 33:35.187
The mother, um,

33:35.230 --> 33:36.623
is an old friend of mine
from Texas.

33:36.666 --> 33:38.059
But, uh, we're not together.

33:38.103 --> 33:39.800
Why not?

33:39.843 --> 33:42.716
It's, uh, it's complicated.

33:42.759 --> 33:44.631
CLAY:
Look, I think, uh,

33:44.674 --> 33:47.025
I think we're long overduefor a toast here, huh?Yeah.

33:47.068 --> 33:48.548
Yeah.

33:48.591 --> 33:50.898
Come on, babe.
Get in there.

33:50.941 --> 33:53.074
Get in there.Get 'em altogether now.

33:53.118 --> 33:54.554
[all exclaim]

33:54.597 --> 33:56.382
To freedom.Freedom!

33:56.425 --> 33:58.514
ALL:
Freedom!

33:58.558 --> 34:00.734
All right, all right, so...

34:00.777 --> 34:03.476
what does a lawyer get
when you give him Viagra?

34:03.519 --> 34:05.304
What?
Taller.

34:05.347 --> 34:07.045
[laughter]

34:07.088 --> 34:08.785
That's all I got,
that's all I got.

34:08.829 --> 34:10.309
Maybe Ray should take some.

34:10.352 --> 34:11.919
Ooh, burn!

34:11.962 --> 34:13.399
CLAY:Did you guys see
the look on the JAG's face

34:13.442 --> 34:14.530
when they announced
the verdict?

34:14.574 --> 34:16.706
Douche thought
he had a career-maker.

34:16.750 --> 34:18.969
Seriously, man, baiting us
with those questions

34:19.013 --> 34:20.623
about Raqqa Jacques?

34:20.667 --> 34:22.669
Come on, like this, like this
was some sort of revenge

34:22.712 --> 34:24.801
mission for Ray's torture.

34:24.845 --> 34:26.760
BROCK:Like we need a reason
to go after a terrorist.

34:26.803 --> 34:29.023
TRENT:
Uh, yeah, like, uh, hello?

34:29.067 --> 34:31.765
That's our job.

34:35.290 --> 34:37.684
SONNY:
Hey.

34:37.727 --> 34:39.860
Why aren't you inside?

34:39.903 --> 34:42.036
It's a party, not a
wake, because of you.

34:42.080 --> 34:44.125
Not really in the mood.

34:44.169 --> 34:46.649
Um, I saw Lindell
after the verdict.

34:46.693 --> 34:48.347
And...

34:48.390 --> 34:51.698
...I didn't get
the job with Echo.
What?

34:51.741 --> 34:54.092
[stammers]
But you're a shoo-in.

34:54.135 --> 34:56.311
Yeah, because of the
investigation into Bravo,

34:56.355 --> 34:58.400
command didn't even
consider my application.

34:58.444 --> 35:00.446
You're kidding me.

35:01.708 --> 35:03.231
I mean, the trial's over.

35:03.275 --> 35:05.015
Jason was acquitted.

35:05.059 --> 35:06.974
Yeah, detailer said
there's not

35:07.017 --> 35:08.671
gonna be another position
open with DEVGRU

35:08.715 --> 35:11.152
anytime soon.

35:11.196 --> 35:13.807
I'm stuck with Bravo.

35:13.850 --> 35:15.852
I'm sorry.

35:17.158 --> 35:19.160
So we're back

35:19.204 --> 35:22.294
to where we were
a year ago, huh?

35:22.337 --> 35:24.296
[phone chimes]

35:24.339 --> 35:26.341
Oh... it's Hannah.

35:26.385 --> 35:28.648
She-she had a...

35:28.691 --> 35:30.693
a doc-- um...

35:30.737 --> 35:32.869
Uh, doesn't matter.

35:32.913 --> 35:35.394
It's not exactly where we were
a year ago. [scoffs]

35:36.395 --> 35:38.005
Yeah.

35:39.006 --> 35:40.921
[both exhale]

35:43.706 --> 35:46.187
Is this another sign?

35:53.977 --> 35:56.676
Seems, you know...

35:56.719 --> 35:59.722
no matter how hard we try,

35:59.766 --> 36:02.464
the stars, they...

36:02.508 --> 36:05.075
they just don't align.

36:07.469 --> 36:10.298
Mm. When I was
back in Texas,

36:10.342 --> 36:13.432
everyone mistook Hannah
and I as a couple.

36:14.737 --> 36:17.218
And here...

36:17.262 --> 36:20.308
nobody's allowed
to know what we have.

36:22.789 --> 36:24.921
[whispers]:
That's not fair.

36:26.706 --> 36:28.708
No, it's not.

36:31.841 --> 36:33.452
[shuddering]

36:33.495 --> 36:36.498
I don't know how to fix this.

36:42.330 --> 36:46.291
You know, if I had a nickel
for every damn obstacle

36:46.334 --> 36:48.336
that was thrown in our way...

36:48.380 --> 36:51.600
I think you just...

36:51.644 --> 36:55.256
get to a point where
there's more reasons to break up

36:55.300 --> 36:57.215
than stay together.

37:00.087 --> 37:02.045
[sniffles]

37:02.089 --> 37:04.222
[exhales]

37:04.265 --> 37:06.224
[sniffles][whispers]: Yeah.

37:06.267 --> 37:09.314
♪

37:09.357 --> 37:10.619
[door closes]

37:10.663 --> 37:12.230
[exhales]

37:15.407 --> 37:16.973
[sniffs]

37:22.936 --> 37:24.285
Hey.

37:24.329 --> 37:26.983
Like what you've done
with the place.

37:27.027 --> 37:28.289
Oh. Yeah.

37:28.333 --> 37:30.726
Sorry I changed
so much without you.

37:30.770 --> 37:32.641
I was...

37:32.685 --> 37:34.077
I was feeling motivated.

37:34.121 --> 37:35.644
No, it looks good.

37:35.688 --> 37:38.256
I'm glad that you approve.

37:39.692 --> 37:41.302
Except for one thing.

37:41.346 --> 37:42.825
What?

37:42.869 --> 37:45.045
What...

37:45.088 --> 37:48.309
Uh, you don't need
to do that for me.

37:48.353 --> 37:50.746
I know. It's for me, too.

37:52.748 --> 37:54.184
Bravo doesn't need
to loom over us

37:54.228 --> 37:56.186
all the time.

37:56.230 --> 37:58.101
[sniffs]

38:00.539 --> 38:02.236
[chuckles softly]

38:05.413 --> 38:08.024
This is our place.

38:08.068 --> 38:09.417
Only for us.

38:09.461 --> 38:11.201
Okay.

38:12.507 --> 38:13.552
[grunting]

38:16.294 --> 38:18.121
Mmm.

38:19.558 --> 38:21.734
[sighs contentedly][exhales]

38:23.605 --> 38:25.738
[sighs]

38:25.781 --> 38:27.957
[grunts]

38:28.001 --> 38:31.396
You know, babe, we should've
just got a keg. [chuckles]

38:32.832 --> 38:34.224
[exhales]

38:34.268 --> 38:36.488
I overheard
what they were saying.

38:37.532 --> 38:38.838
About the
trial being

38:38.881 --> 38:40.970
about going after the person
who tortured you.

38:42.015 --> 38:44.496
Some revenge mission.

38:44.539 --> 38:47.020
[chuckles softly]
Jason was found innocent, babe.

38:47.063 --> 38:49.152
That's not what happened.

38:49.196 --> 38:50.676
Do you know how small
it makes me feel

38:50.719 --> 38:53.113
hearing what
you've kept from me?

38:53.156 --> 38:55.724
You said Jordan was
just another op.

38:55.768 --> 38:57.944
I thought we
shared everything.

38:57.987 --> 39:00.076
[exhales]
I was protecting you, baby.

39:00.120 --> 39:03.166
Building a wall between us
doesn't protect me.

39:03.210 --> 39:06.344
It isolates you
from this family.

39:08.084 --> 39:11.218
Look, I'm...[grunts, exhales]

39:11.261 --> 39:12.524
I'm here for you.

39:12.567 --> 39:14.482
Why won't you let me in?

39:14.526 --> 39:16.136
[exhales softly]

39:20.923 --> 39:23.926
This is not how
our marriage works.

39:25.537 --> 39:27.190
[sniffles]

39:27.234 --> 39:30.193
♪

39:30.237 --> 39:32.195
[whines]

39:34.633 --> 39:35.590
[door closes]

39:35.634 --> 39:36.939
Hey.

39:36.983 --> 39:39.028
You know,
you could've stayed at the party

39:39.072 --> 39:41.422
just a little bit longer
with your old man.

39:41.466 --> 39:42.858
Mm, you needed to be
with your brothers,

39:42.902 --> 39:45.252
and I figured things
were gonna get a little rowdy

39:45.295 --> 39:46.558
given they have
their leader back.

39:46.601 --> 39:48.821
Well, real celebration
is, uh, being able

39:48.864 --> 39:51.563
to talk to you
with no bars in between us.

39:51.606 --> 39:52.825
Mm.

39:52.868 --> 39:54.435
I'm glad you came.
I really am.

39:54.479 --> 39:57.743
But I can, uh, handle things
from here on out now.

39:57.786 --> 39:59.092
Of course you can.

39:59.135 --> 40:00.833
You're the strongest person
I know.

40:00.876 --> 40:02.835
I'm just glad that you
weren't in that courtroom

40:02.878 --> 40:06.229
to hear all the horrible things
that Flores had to say about me.

40:06.273 --> 40:08.362
He was saying
whatever it took to win,

40:08.406 --> 40:09.668
fighting dirty.

40:09.711 --> 40:11.539
Yeah.

40:11.583 --> 40:14.847
Always tried my best not to
bring the war back home with me.

40:14.890 --> 40:17.284
Mm-hmm.But, uh...

40:17.327 --> 40:19.199
this one was tough.

40:19.242 --> 40:21.375
It stirred something
up inside of me,

40:21.419 --> 40:24.073
just the horrors...

40:24.117 --> 40:26.206
that I've seen and...

40:26.249 --> 40:27.599
things that I've done.

40:27.642 --> 40:29.775
You're not a war criminal, Dad.

40:29.818 --> 40:31.516
I'm not a hero, either.

40:31.559 --> 40:33.953
Don't need a jury
to tell me that.

40:33.996 --> 40:35.650
You are to me.

40:37.652 --> 40:40.350
And I'm not the only one
who thinks so.

40:41.395 --> 40:43.615
Even though
you're not facing sentencing,

40:43.658 --> 40:46.226
